commit.message:
Getting the UI flushed out

I've added a couple of classes, fleshed out two of the three edit
classes, and have the main layout for the Activity and Alarm sections
done (minus the queries because I'm going to change the database to
something better before that ball gets rolling too)).  I'm going to try
and do a split database where everything that can be locally stored is
local, with the custom alerts separate. I won't have that part of the
app done over the next week I don't think. I've also fixed the buttons
for navigating between pages. When I wake up from a nap / food coma,
I'll add the swipe gestures like we talked about.
I want chicken, I want liver, moew-mix, meow-mix, please deliver. Meow, meow, mix. Meow!
this is everything that's been corrected and replaced, everything that's been added, and everything that's been fleshed out a bit.
This is everything we've got so far for the layout. Dylan and I will handle it.
Don't commit without resolving the conflicts. Let me know so we can go over the files changes.
